font.font: The client attends the Provider's service delivery centre for an appointment.

span.font: Client has been advised previously about the reasons for completing the measure.

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 398px; height: 1px; padding-top: 257px; margin-left: 103px;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.span: A mobile device can be used to navigate to the link provided by the QR code.

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 398px; height: 1px; padding-top: 337px; margin-left: 102px;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.font: The client can be given a tablet to fill out the measure in the waiting room or during their appointment.

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 398px; height: 1px; padding-top: 417px; margin-left: 102px;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.b: Completed measure is uploaded in other systems

font.font: The completed questionnaire is automatically uploaded into the CIMS and a report can be emailed to the appropriate service provider.

div.span: The report does not include personal client details. The email will include a code that the psychologist can use to match to their client records.

switch.text: Completed measure is uploaded in other systems...

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 398px; height: 1px; padding-top: 87px; margin-left: 101px;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.span: When the client arrives for their appointment, a member of staff can enter the CIMS, create a new file for the client (if it is their first appointment) and generate what in OMSSS is called a 'collection'.

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 398px; height: 1px; padding-top: 177px; margin-left: 101px;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.font: The CIMS will use the OMSSS API to request a new collection, generating a QR code.
